sentences: Jeff Scott Soto (born November 4, 1965) is an American rock singer of Puerto Rican descent.
He is best known for being the vocalist on Yngwie Malmsteen's first two albums, and (briefly) the lead vocalist for Journey in 2006–2007.
In 1982, after performing in several local cover bands, Soto recorded several songs as lead singer for the band Kanan.
In 1984, Soto provided vocals for virtuoso guitarist Yngwie Malmsteen's debut album Rising Force and his next album Marching Out a year later.
Soto performed at the 2000 annual OIQFC 'Freddie Mercury Birthday Party' at Reading in the UK, where he performed "Dragon Attack" with Brian May.
In 2012 Taylor hired Soto as one of the four singers chosen for the official tribute band Queen Extravaganza.
Soto's solo album Damage Control was released on Frontiers Records in March 2012.
His next solo album SOTO was released on January 30, 2015.
In 2016, they released DIVAK on earMusic.
They toured afterwards, opening for Winery Dogs in May 2016.
In 2015, Soto recorded vocals for Joel Hoekstra's 13, contributing to the album Dying to Live.
In 2018, SOTO recorded their 3rd album Origami, released in May 2019.
In 2018, SOTO recorded their 3rd album Origami, released in May 2019.
Soto released another solo album, Retribution in November 2017.
In early 2020 he completed work on his 7th solo album as well as scheduled a live album for release in July.

2020 sees the release of 2 solo albums on Frontiers Records, "Jeff Scott Soto - Loud & Live In Milan 2019", recorded live at the annual Frontiers Rock Festival and "Wide Awake (In My Dreamland)" co-written and produced by Alessandro Del Vecchio.

2020 sees the release of 2 solo albums on Frontiers Records, "Jeff Scott Soto - Loud & Live In Milan 2019", recorded live at the annual Frontiers Rock Festival and "Wide Awake (In My Dreamland)" co-written and produced by Alessandro Del Vecchio.
Soto was one of the founding members of Talisman in 1989.
He was in the group up until their disbandment in 2007.
Talisman regrouped in December 2019 to record a tribute track for  bassist Marcel Jacob on the 10th anniversary of his death.
In 2006, Soto replaced Steve Augeri in Journey after Augeri left the tour due to an acute throat infection.
After months of being a tour replacement, Soto was officially hired as the band's singer in December 2006.
However, the stint was short-lived, as he was fired from the band on June 12, 2007.
Soto joined Trans-Siberian Orchestra as a touring singer in 2008.
The group, named after the initials of the band involved, Soto's representing Talisman, released a self-titled debut album in November 2009.
In 2013, they released their second album Rise Up, and their third studio album Earthrage followed in 2018.
In 2013, they released their second album Rise Up, and their third studio album Earthrage followed in 2018.
They began recording a new album in 2020.
In May 2017, he joined a progressive metal supergroup named Sons of Apollo with Derek Sherinian, bassist Billy Sheehan, drummer Mike Portnoy and guitarist Ron "Bumblefoot" Thal.
Their debut album, Psychotic Symphony, was released Oct 20, 2017 with Inside Out/Sony.
After releasing a live album in 2019, Sons of Apollo released their second album MMXX in January 2020.
After releasing a live album in 2019, Sons of Apollo released their second album MMXX in January 2020.

In 2020, alongside his Sons Of Apollo co-bandmate Billy Sheehan, Soto was invited by a Glendale, California based Armenian guitarist Hovak Alaverdyan to participate in his progressive metal project Octavision.
The album titled Coexist was released on 29th December 2020.
In 2012, he married his long-term girlfriend Elena.

Currently he works as solo artist, with his self-named band SOTO and as the vocalist of super-groups W.E.T., Sons of Apollo and  Trans-Siberian Orchestra.
In 1984, Soto provided vocals for virtuoso guitarist Yngwie Malmsteen's debut album Rising Force and his next album Marching Out a year later.
Soto performed at the 2000 annual OIQFC 'Freddie Mercury Birthday Party' at Reading in the UK, where he performed "Dragon Attack" with Brian May.
Soto then appeared with Brian May and Roger Taylor at the 'Hollywood Walk of Fame' bash for the Official International Queen Fan Club.
In early 2020 he completed work on his 7th solo album as well as scheduled a live album for release in July.
After months of being a tour replacement, Soto was officially hired as the band's singer in December 2006.
